concept_explanation.safe_schema_evolution:
**Evolving schemas safely — real examples:**

```json
// VERSION 1 (current):
{"fields": [
  {"name": "tradeId",  "type": "string"},
  {"name": "symbol",   "type": "string"},
  {"name": "price",    "type": "double"}
]}

// VERSION 2 — SAFE: add field with default:
{"fields": [
  {"name": "tradeId",    "type": "string"},
  {"name": "symbol",     "type": "string"},
  {"name": "price",      "type": "double"},
  {"name": "totalValue", "type": "double", "default": 0.0},  ← NEW, with default
  {"name": "sector",     "type": ["null","string"], "default": null}  ← nullable
]}
// Schema Registry: COMPATIBLE ✓
// Old consumers: see totalValue=0.0 (default) — safe
// New consumers: see actual totalValue — correct

// VERSION 3 — UNSAFE: rename 'price' to 'unitPrice':
{"fields": [
  {"name": "tradeId",  "type": "string"},
  {"name": "symbol",   "type": "string"},
  {"name": "unitPrice", "type": "double"}  ← renamed from 'price'
]}
// Schema Registry: INCOMPATIBLE ✗ — old consumers look for 'price', not 'unitPrice'
// FIX: keep 'price' AND add 'unitPrice' with default,
//      then remove 'price' in a LATER version
```

step_by_step_solution.details:
```properties
spring.kafka.producer.value-serializer=io.confluent.kafka.serializers.KafkaAvroSerializer
spring.kafka.producer.properties.schema.registry.url=http://localhost:8081
```

```java
@Service
public class TradeEventPublisher {
    private final KafkaTemplate<String, TradeExecutedEvent> kafkaTemplate;

    public void publishTrade(String tradeId, String symbol, int qty,
                              double price, TradeType type) {
        // Build from generated Avro class:
        TradeExecutedEvent event = TradeExecutedEvent.newBuilder()
            .setTradeId(tradeId)
            .setUserId("U01")
            .setSymbol(symbol)
            .setQty(qty)
            .setPrice(price)
            .setTotalValue(qty * price)
            .setTradeType(type)
            .build();

        kafkaTemplate.send("trade-executed", symbol, event);
    }
}
```

worked_example.final_code:
// 1. TradeExecutedEvent.avsc: Avro schema with all fields
// 2. pom.xml: avro-maven-plugin generates Java class from .avsc
// 3. application.properties: KafkaAvroSerializer + schema.registry.url
// 4. Publisher: builds event using generated builder API
// 5. Consumer: @KafkaListener with generated TradeExecutedEvent type
// 6. Schema v2: adds 'sector' field with null default → backward compatible
// 7. Schema Registry rejects: renaming 'price' → 'unitPrice' (breaking change)

